The Bank of England said it provided themoney market with assistance worth 90 mln stg in response to anearly round of bill offers from discount houses.    Earlier, the bank estimated the shortage in the systemtoday at some 1.05 billion stg.    The bank bought bills for resale to the market in equalamounts on April 1, 2 and 3 at an interest rate of 10-7/16 pct. REUTER&#3;